string  - '2'

what is the purpose of a JenkinsFile?
   - Test constatnt in code is unaffected
   - Continuous Integration
    - coding standards
    - Jenkins enforces these standards
    - SonarScan, see if there are any vulnerabilities in the code
    - Unit Testing
    - Maintain histroy of each commit's build process


Things to remember:

- Jenkins is a layer between your new code and the sanity of the production application
- where will one push the code?

can I not use a framework for this to make my life easier?

CI/CD framework, with Jenkins as a tool

  - github
    - how will code from github travel from github to the remote machine?
      - webhook
        - what triggers the webhook?
          - a new commit pushes to the webhook
            - how will the webhook know where to deploy?
              -send the hostname
                - what if I have 100s of machines?

                - what if I want to scale up/down the system?
                  - create a file with all the 100s of hosts
                  - when deploying all the hosts receives the brand new code


































